  "number": 2699,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2699",
  "title": "fix(perf): only compute snappoints when step is provided",
  "body": "This keeps the snapping but does not generate the snap points if no value is provided. We can do that because rheostat snaps the point to the rounded value by default (if `snap=true`). Until rheostat provides a lazy way to fix the snappoints, there will be a risk of having an \"out of memory\" error because the range of values can be too big. There is an open issue opened for adding this new API: airbnb/rheostat#14 but it's uncertain if someone will work on it.\r\n\r\nFix #2662",
